title: THE I-LAND: Netflix's Worst Show Ever!
author: Think Story
comment: Remember kids: someone wrote this, someone got paid for it.
The idea isn't half-bad, could be incredibly interesting if they made it more about how psycho some of them are, instead of drama. Sad that this unique idea wasn't executed well.
can we talk about the fact that, despite all of them being washed up on a beach, none of them are wet or even dirty?
Netflix seriously needs to focus more on quality, not quantity. Even their decent movies all have the exact same bland color scheme, makes it look like all the color was bled out of the frame.
"You'll never see your kids again" UNO REVERSE CARD
description:
In this video we look at the absolute trainwreck  that is Netflix's "The I-Land." With terrible acting, dialogue, and plot, I break the show down so you don't have to.
